### Critical Note — `gatherAppContext()` Migration

When migrating `services/claudeService.ts`, the `gatherAppContext()` function currently reads from 14+ AsyncStorage keys and assembles the full context string passed to Claude on every cabinet and check-in request. This is the most important function in the codebase — if it produces incorrect or empty context, the cabinet's responses will be degraded and it won't be immediately obvious why.

Migrate this function carefully:
1. It must remain async
2. It must read from Supabase (using the authenticated user's data) instead of AsyncStorage
3. Its output format (the plain-text context string) must not change — Claude depends on the exact formatting
4. Explicitly verify it returns correct data after migration before proceeding to the next phase

